< p > We have applied so called strict layering which means that the layers can only access the classes directly beneath them . This leads the solution to create an additional set of DT Os ( < code > Cake Info </ code >, < code > Cake Topping Info </ code >, < code > Cake Layer Info </ code >) to translate data between layers . In other words , < code > Cake Baking Service </ code > cannot return entities ( < code > Cake </ code >, < code > Cake Topping </ code >, < code > Cake Layer </ code >) directly since these reside on data access layer but instead translates these into business layer DT Os (< code > Cake Info </ code >, < code > Cake Topping Info </ code >, < code > Cake Layer Info </ code >) and returns them instead . This way the presentation layer does not have any knowledge of other layers than the business layer and thus is not affected by changes to them .
